   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition">
                <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
                    <lb n="2"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Publius">
                     <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublio</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Rufinus">Rufino</name>
                  <lb n="3"/>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Sucessus">Sucesso</name>
               </persName>;
                    <lb n="4"/> vixit <expan><abbr>ann</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
               <lb n="5"/> plus <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>inus</ex></expan>
               <num xml:lang="lat" value="60">LX</num>.
                    <lb n="6"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Aviana">Aviania</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Maximillia">Ma
                    <lb n="7" break="no"/> ximillia</name>
               </persName>
               <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>i<supplied reason="lost">u</supplied><lb n="8" break="no"/>gi</abbr></expan> suo <expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>ene</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erenti</ex></expan>.
                    <lb n="9"/>
               <handShift/>
               <add place="bottom">A 
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Clodia">Clodia</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Felicissima">Felic<unclear>i</unclear>
                     <supplied reason="lost">ssima</supplied>
                  </name>
                  <lb n="10"/>
                  <expan><abbr>locu</abbr><ex>s</ex></expan>
                  <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>onatus</ex></expan>.</add>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Divine Spirits. To Publius Rufinus Sucessus; he lived for more or less sixty
               years. Aviania Maximillia (made this) for her well-deserving husband. The place was
               given by Clodia Felic[issima]. </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>
               <seg type="material">Gray and light brown marble</seg> (Tuck).</p>
            <p>Line 9: A(ula) Clodia (Tuck)</p>
            <p>Line 10: locu(m) d(onavit) (Tuck) </p>
            <p>The formula <hi rend="italic">locus datus</hi> occurs fairly commonly at the
               end of inscriptions, although it is unusual for the ablative agent to precede it.
               This inscription is also the only attestation of <hi rend="italic">locus datus</hi> abbreviated as LOCV D in EDCS.</p>
         </div>
